Level of decussation of superior cerebellar peduncle is midbrain. The decussation of superior cerebellar peduncle is the crossing of fibers of the superior cerebellar peduncle across the midline, and is located at the level of the inferior colliculi of midbrain.<br />
<br />
&nbsp;
<p><i>Reference: Gray&#39;s Anatomy The Anatomical Basis Of Clinical Practice Edition 42 nd Page no 432,455</i></p>
<br />
&nbsp;

The sixth aortic arch is a part of the aortic arch system which forms during fetal development. When the distal part of this aortic arch on the right side disappears, the right recurrent laryngeal nerve needs to find a new route, and so it hooks around the right subclavian artery. On the left side, the nerve remains in its original position and hooks around the ligamentum arteriosum, which is the remnant of the distal part of the left sixth aortic arch.<br />
<br />
&nbsp;
<p><i>Reference: Langman&#39; Medical Embryology Edition 14 th page no 209</i></p>
<br />
&nbsp;
